### Anything else relevant?

I think the issue is because Angular type checker does not import the type of the component directly, instead it uses TypeScripts AST and copies only the class decleration (see [here ](https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/main/packages/compiler-cli/src/ngtsc/typecheck/src/environment.ts#L65) and [here](https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/main/packages/compiler-cli/src/ngtsc/typecheck/src/type_check_file.ts#L81)). The code does not take into account the possibility of decleration merging.

The project I am working on is using Stencil as a component library. The Stencil Angular output target uses declaration merging in its output which breaks template type checking. My first instinct was to report an issue in the stencil repo, but I think it would be better if Angular supported the expected behaviour of typescript.

