### Anything else?

I'm currently working around this issue by using the following middleware, which changes the req.url for any .css.map files to the root path. So 'about/home.component.css.map' becomes '/home.component.css.map'. 



fix-css-map-url.ts
```
import { RequestHandler } from 'express';

export const fixCssMapUrl: RequestHandler = (req, res, next) => {
    try {
        if (req.url.endsWith('.css.map')) {
            const originalUrl = req.url;
            req.url = '/' + originalUrl.split('/').pop();
        }
        next();
    } catch (error) {
        next(error);
    }
};
```

server.ts
```
import { fixCssMapUrl } from './middleware/fix-css-map-url';

app.use(fixCssMapUrl);

app.get('**', express.static(browserDistFolder, { maxAge: '1y', index: 'index.html' }));
```

### Feature Description

It would be great if we can have a `dir` signal.

Currently, to convert into a proper signal I have to do use `toSignal` in `ngOnInit`.

```ts
ngOnInit(): void {
  runInInjectionContext(this.injector, () => {
      this.direction = toSignal<Direction, Direction>(this.dir.change.pipe(map(() => this.dir.value)), { initialValue: this.dir.value });
  });
}
```

### Use Case

I want to be able to determine dir value as well as re-calculating stuff when dir changes, a combination of `dir.value` and `dir.changes`, a `dir()` signal inside `effect()` is needed.
